This is related to #13258.

While implementing this property, which by the way works amazingly well for Form, see GIF below, I was wondering:

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4cf06edf-59d1-4ae7-b488-4685031040f4)

Since, as I predicted, this is working only on Top-Level Windows, which equals "Form" in WinForms, and we also already have the properties `FormCornerPreference`, `FormBorderColor`, `FormCaptionBackColor`, `FormCaptionTextColor` if we should rename:

`ScreenCaptionMode` -> `FormScreenCaptureMode`

But I _would_ actually rather leave the enum like this:

```
namespace System.Windows.Forms;

/// <summary>
///  Enumeration defining the behavior when a form or control is captured in a screenshot.
/// </summary>
public enum ScreenCaptureMode
{
    /// <summary>
    ///  The form or control can be captured normally in screenshots. Default.
    /// </summary>
    Allow = 0,

    /// <summary>
    ///  The form or control appears blacked out in screenshots.
    /// </summary>
    HideContent = 1,

    /// <summary>
    ///  The form or control appears blurred in screenshots.
    /// Requires Windows 10 version 2004 or higher.
    /// </summary>
    HideWindow = 2
}
```
